-- Chile’s Government to Propose Tax Changes by April, Emol Reports
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-01-10T17:53:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/chile-s-government-to-propose-tax-changes-by-april-emol-reports.html
Chile’s government  will propose
changes to the  tax code  by April, after holding talks with
different political parties, newspaper  El Mercurio  reported on
its website  Emol , citing government spokesman Andres Chadwick.  The government won’t give in to calls from members of the
governing coalition to reduce fuel taxes, the Santiago-based
newspaper  reported , without saying which taxes President
Sebastian Pinera is willing to modify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
